Our Barre classes use a combination of postures inspired by ballet and other disciplines like yoga and Pilates. The barre is used as a prop to balance while doing exercises that focus on isometric strength training (holding your body still while you contract a specific set of muscles) combined with high reps of small range-of-motion movements." All our instructors are prof. and classical educated dancers !

Our Barre classes use a combination of postures inspired by ballet and other disciplines like yoga and Pilates. The barre is used as a prop to balance while doing exercises that focus on isometric strength training (holding your body still while you contract a specific set of muscles) combined with high reps of small range-of-motion movements." All our instructors are prof. and classical educated dancers !

To symbolize my graditude, you get a picture of this giant door-knocker, mostly for decoration I guess, but what an entrance - theres one at each side of the gate to this Courtyard !The church tower you see in the background is the one on Nikolaj Kirke. Actually not the original, because originally it looked more like a tower on a medieval castle. This one is added in 1909, to a church that was burned down in the late 1700 century, rebuild and hasn't functioned as a church since 1805. Today you'll find various art exhibitions in there. And no matter what kind, its worth a visit, just to see the church from inside.Busy morning in the city center.ğŸ’¨ But weekend is almost here. Happy Friday to all of you!âœ¨âœ¨âœ¨
